The Strandline Compact's dual-attestation protocol was designed, in part, to prevent the kind of single-authority record manipulation that destroyed the corridor's court systems: the Sultan's Palace's Corrective Harmonization is the explicit negative example in Ledger House institutional history.
Mafdet's dual-provenance classification for corridor artifacts — oasis-provenance, pyramid-provenance, and dual-origin objects carrying both signatures — provides the most detailed commercial taxonomy for eastern desert materials in current practice.
