Cargo origin attestation for materials marked as eastern desert provenance requires traceable documentation through at least one oasis authentication point; artifacts without this documentation are classified as eastern desert corridor uncertain, reducing commercial value by a standard margin.
Mafdet's maritime insurance rates for corridor artifact cargo are calibrated against corridor stability indicators; the three oasis flow reports are the primary data sources for this calibration.
The Ledger House's position on the Black Sun Shard connection: classified as an academic matter of interest to specialist buyers; the practical commercial concern is provenance integrity, not cosmological context.

